{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"Active scan mode (speed + latency per point)\n      When enabled, each recorded point runs a quick gateway ping and short speed test. Slower but richer data.","choice":"active-mode","id":null,"timestamp":1773184103932}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"Nearby AP list (CoreWLAN scan)\n      CoreWLAN can scan and return all visible access points with RSSI, channel, band, BSSID. Shows a list of detected APs in the sidebar.","choice":"nearby-aps","id":null,"timestamp":1773184107780}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"Per-AP heatmap filter\n      When you have multiple APs, show the heatmap for a specific BSSID only. Lets you compare coverage zones of AP1 vs AP2.","choice":"ap-filter","id":null,"timestamp":1773184111679}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"Project save / load\n      Save named survey projects to disk (JSON + image). Open previous projects. Project list shown via File menu or open sheet.","choice":"project-save","id":null,"timestamp":1773184112300}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"Channel / band visualization\n      Color each measurement dot by frequency band (blue = 5 GHz, orange = 2.4 GHz, green = 6 GHz). Quick visual scan of band distribution.","choice":"channel-viz","id":null,"timestamp":1773184129101}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"Coverage threshold indicator\n      Set a minimum acceptable RSSI (e.g., -70 dBm). Areas below threshold shown with a hatched red overlay. NetSpot's \"zones of poor coverage.\"","choice":"coverage-threshold","id":null,"timestamp":1773184129662}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"Hover tooltip on measurement points\n      Hover over a recorded dot to see all its data (RSSI, SNR, channel, timestamp, speed if active). Like NetSpot's popover.","choice":"point-tooltip","id":null,"timestamp":1773184130114}
